 That's a beautiful young lady to send away in a coach at night , Mr . Darnay ! he said , handling his new glass . 
 Yes , said Mr . Darnay , frowning slightly . 
 How does it feel to have such a beautiful young woman pity you and weep for you ? Is it worth being put on trial for your life to be the object of such sympathy and compassion , Mr . Darnay ? 
 Again Darnay didn't answer . 
 She was very happy to receive your message when I gave it to her . She didn't show that she was pleased , but I think she was . 
 This comment reminded Darnay that Carton had helped him by delivering this message . He turned the conversation to that fact and thanked him for his help . 
 I don't want or deserve any thanks , he said casually . First of all , it was nothing . And second , I don't even know why I did it . Let me ask you a question , Mr . Darnay . 
 Of course . It's the least I could do for your favor . 
 Do you think that I like you ? 
 Really , Mr . Carton , answered Mr . Darnay , a bit flustered by the question , I haven't thought much about it . 
 Think about it now . 
 You have acted as if you liked me , but I don't think you actually do . 
